Table 1. Comparison with SOTA methods on landmark detection accuracy. We report NME (%) on 300W, COFW and AFLW. On WFLW, 
both NME (%) and FR (%) at the threshold of 10% are reported. Our method achieved the best accuracy on most datasets by simply 
using ResNet-18 as the backbone, and the second best on 300W-Common subset. DTLD uses the basic decoder, while DTLD+ adopts the 
parallel decoder. DTLD-s has all parameters trained from scratch. The top methods are coordinate regression-based while the middle ones 
are heatmap-based.
